values:
it's been a relatively long time since i'd posted last.  to define "relatively"--
--long enough for livejournal to forget me
--long enough for me to forget livejournal (my username, password, etc.  took me a good ten-second stare at the computer 
  screen before it all came back to me.)
--exactly fifty days (pretty cool coincidence, if you ask me)
--long enough for me to be afraid to post, worried that this post wouldn't be worth the fifty day wait.  (i worry about
  that kind of stuff.  i'm a weird person.)
--by the way, what is it with me and my love of lists in this blog?
--fyi, i added that last one just to make my list look more list-y, a mighty five lister (well, now it has six items) 
  rather than an insignificant four lister. 

well, i'm too tired to try and transition between the following things, so here's another list of what's new:
--i've decided songs don't always need to include some profound lyrics to be a good song
--journalism is slowly killing me via sleep deprivation.  it's not a great way to go.
--crew, the frightening ghost of months past, is creeping up slowly but steadily.  why do i do it if i dread it so much?  
  why i do anything, nowadays.  it looks good on a college ap, duh.
--i'm pretty sure i made my guitar teacher think i'm suicidal, which i'm not.  i just sang her this song, which actually 
  has a very happy tune, and is supposed to be kind of making light of death, like hispanics do during cinco de mayo.
  all i wanna do is lie in bed
  no school
  just me and my dreams
  a whole day sleeping
  horizontal...undercovers...undiscovered

  something happens in my head
  when i realize that i am dead
  it is such bliss
  you don't wanna miss this
  i can't figure it out
  it's like a heaven with all these angels about
  i can't explain
  something happens in my brain
--wow, i just remembered i've written like forty songs since i last posted, maybe i'll get those up sometime.
--i have a new love interest.  i even improv-ed a song for him, because i'm cool like that.  i'll give you the first 
  verse, because it's humor is too, too true.
  (tune to the blues :) )
  well i have this crazy pain
  it kinda feels like the bends
  because the guy that i really like
  is really liked by all my friends...
  (sigh, shall i list them off for you?  at least his constant admirers are a way to prove his worth, but it does make him 
  very inaccessible.  :(  whenever i'm around him, five other girls will be running after us and consequently trampling me 
  painfully.  i've tried to "push" my way back to his side, but i always hesitate and the opportunity's gone.  i always 
  hesitate because i realize i'm being aggressive, and i've never been aggressive before.  at all.  wow, teenage hormones 
  never fail to amuse.
--i'm REALLY into latin music.  my new loves--cafe tacuba and kinky.  plus, the fact that latino guys are really hot may 
  have had something to do with my interest/obsession.  diego luna, anyone? (this, um, by the way, doesn't suggest AT ALL
  (heh heh) that the aforementioned guy is hispanic.  at all.)

well, i wanted this post to be captivating, deep, moving, and hilarious on top of it all.  sorry i've made this day an even bigger failure than it was before.

p.s.  haha, i was so tired (see mood) that i originally posted this mood as "touched."  i'm cool, no doubt about it.

i'm strangely proud of myself.  today i've semi-skipped my second class of my otherwise flawless academic career.  hehe, i can feel my chest swelling up with pride at this.  i split fifth period, meaning that for the first forty-five minutes (of the ninety minutes allotted to lunch and fifth period) i take band, and the second half i take journalism.  on block day, after half of band we go to lunch, except i go to journalism.  this is all very confusing of course.  actually, the only point to finishing this story is to explain why i've only "semi-skipped," if this doesn't interest you i permit you to stop reading at this time.
anyway, to continue, when we went to lunch today i checked in at journalism, we were doing nothing, so i went home without returning to band.  yay!  wow, in retrospect, that was a really lame anecdote.  my apologies for straining your brain in an effort to comprehend my incomprehensible thoughts.

ok, you know what i just discovered about myself?  i don't believe in a soulmate, true love, love at first sight, any of that crap.  all these things have been hammered into me, and on what grounds?  do you honestly think you're parents fell in love with each other when they first saw each other, or was it just hormones?  that's what everything seems to boil down to, just a chemical reaction/imbalance in the brain.  

     i think that what i think (haha, i make no sense) is there are many people out there who have a personality that would mesh well with mine, some who will be a perfect fit, but if i find one it's just chance, not some incredible sign from the magical deities above.  and now i'm done talking.  i probably should go, considering i haven't started my homework yet.

here is the (dun du-du-dun!) brand new unveiling of the long-anticipated public version of brittney's livejournal!  ok, i know you guys aren't that excited, but i'm having fun here, so bear with me.  here are the well, edited versions of my past twenty-something entries to make them pg-13.  :)  anyways, yeah!  look around, and enjoy.

it's been a heckuva long time since i've entered in this thing. (did i really just use the word "heckuva?" wow, i must be more tired than i thought i was.) well, i'm just doin' the usual, puttin' off homework and the like. (where is this southern drawl-type coming from?!?!) anyway, just browsin' my bro's journal when i came across this jewel, and i had to try it out. a 'i've visited more states than you' map. hopefully this will work. if not, you will finally understand how technology-challenged i truly am. (rivaled only by my geography-challengosity. try to say that one five times fast.)

<img src="http://www.world66.com/myworld66/visitedStates/statemap?visited=AKAZCACOCTDCDEHIIDMEMDMAMIMTNVNHNJNMNYORPARIUTVTVAWA"><br/>

<a href="http://douweosinga.com/projects/visitedstates">create your own visited states map</a>

 or <a href="http://douweosinga.com/projects/googlehacks">check out these Google Hacks.</a>

oh, by the way, I MADE CREW TEAM CAPTAIN!!!!!! WOO HOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!! (whew, glad i got that out of my system.) (have you noticed the strange amounts of parentheses in this entry? whatever.)

hey, if i can't find mine i might as well get wrapped up in somebody else's.  and who cares if that person is fictional?

another snow day today.  more like a slush day.  when i walked to my friends' houses, i practically fell at least a dozen times.  this afternoon we went to a movie, titled "Something's Gotta Give," starring jack nicholson and diane keaton.  let me tell you, they were PHENOMENAL!  i mean, i know that normally i would hate a guy like jack nicholson's character, but he plays him so well that i actually felt sympathetic for him when things went wrong in his life.  in the real world no one is all good or all bad, but in the acting world it takes a superb actor to make the viewer understand that about life.  whoa, now i'm getting all philosophical.  a good movie will do that to me.  a bad one just makes me tired and yawn. 

god, i've never been so emotionally involved in a movie!  i literally felt their pain and their joy.  wow.  interesting.

anyway, baked chocolate chip cookies today!  they are absolutely scrumptious (sp?) in every sense of the word.  back to school tomorrow, and now i'm having such a good time that i'm kind of disappointed.  oh well.  hasta.  (by the way, "hasta" means see you in spanish.  i'm crazy about the language!  estoy loca de la lengua!)

after fifteen years and forty-two days on this planet, i have come to this conclusion.  life sucks.  or maybe it's just that my life sucks right now.  why won't my freakin' parents just leave me the heck alone!?!?!  a poem to illustrate my emotions (if you haven't noticed, i like writing poetry.):

Hate For You

     comes so strong

     it knocks the breath out of my lungs

     it unfurls, hurling itself in all directions

     inside the pit of my stomach

     like an explosion

     contained only by unbelievable

     self-restraint,

     with which i hide

     my anger.

     I loathe

       despise and

       abhor

       you.

yeah, i'm a real happy person.  anyways, my friends and i had a good time today, at least.  we went sledding, had snowball fights, and the like.  i even lost a game of clue!  woo hoo!  well, hasta.

p. s. it was a snow day today, therefore the snow-based activities.

this time my dad and i were out on a really really emphasis on really busy arterial, and all of a sudden he commands me to make a lane change.  earlier we had been practicing the infamous backing around a corner (see previous entry) so my right side view mirror was tilted all the way down to the ground.  i quickly glanced over at the mirror, of course saw no cars because i was looking at a small square of asphalt, and turned.  um, not smart.  i came about two inches from hitting a car in the next lane, who thankfully recognized my inadequacy early on and swerved out of the way.  but, don't worry, you won't have to stay indoors all the time to avoid the national emergency of me driving.  i will definitely make sure my mirrors are properly adjusted from now on.  hmm...maybe i'll make that my new new year's resolution.  it is "self-helpish."

well, school starts tomorrow.  can't say i'm disappointed.  (see previous entries if hopelessly confused)

try it!  i double triple quadruple puppy dog dare you!

today was *shudder* my driving lesson with *shudder* His Devilishness, Tim the Evil.  i swear, he has it out to get me.  he always sets the lessons up so that i am forced to do all the difficult stuff.  for example, he allowed my precious cousin to do

her backing around a corner at his "favorite corner."  honest to god, that's what he called it, because it has a sidewalk all the way around, and it has high visiblilty.  she, of course, backed around perfectly.  he makes me do it at a corner with a big bush jutting out into my line of vision, and there is no curb!  coincidence?  i think not!  obviously his satanic master has told him that in ruining my driving experience he will end up with a better slot in the afterlife.  anyway, my mom and i were chatting afterward, more like i was venting and she was painfully listening.  she told me that this situation was a good thing, because my cousin, the perfect driver, isn't used to being the "good student" who gets all the praise.  she's usually the one who feels like i do now, second-rate.  vise versa for me.  so maybe i should allow her to graciously soak up the  praise, while i sit back and remember i'm good at other things.  i promise mother i will do this until my head blows off, at which point i'm not responsible for any damage i inflict on the devil-driver.

hmm...maybe before the next lesson i'll write a nice disclaimer/warning on his windshield.  nah, that'd be a waste of good spray paint.

anyways, otherwise i'm doing ok.  school's almost here, yes!  for once i'm not being sarcastic.  oh, and it snowed today!  double yes!  of course, it was about 4 millimeters' worth, but whatever.  i'm not going to complain about that, i have enough on my complain plate.

well, i knew what i wanted to write about, it was right on the tip of my tongue, or given the situation i guess one might say it was right on the tips of my fingers.  but, since i can't think of it, i'll just give you a poem i wrote a few days ago when i was stuck in an emotional "slump."  i don't really know what's wrong with me lately.  actually, i do know what's wrong with me.  mis padres estan volviendome loca!!!  ellos siempre estan preguntando a mi para hacer los quehaceres.  no me gustan los quehaceres para nada!  o, y creo que me gusta este chico, pero vive en un estado muy diferente y esta muy lejos de washington.  yo miss el.*  oh well.  here's the poem.

     Untitled

     my nocturnal nature    

     morphed me into

     a lone wolf

     who delights in

     howling at the

     midnight stars

     while avoiding the

     frolicking day-pups

     whose happiness

     annoys me.

i guess you've probably pinned me as a sardonic, depressed little party-pooper, so i feel i should tell you i'm a lot happier at school with my friends.  odd, isn't it?

oh, by the way, i bought my tolo dress today.  it's kinda cute, black with this pink flower design.  too tired to feel excited, though.

*in spanish to avoid certain people understanding it.  *cough cough* trevor *cough cough*

i know it's probably not considered "cool" to post three times in one day, but it's not like anyone's going to read this anyway. thought i should state this while it is still new years, that my new year's resolution is to post at least once a week. you (the non-existent being that you are) are thinking, well that's not very self-helpish. well, this will help me "express myself and develop my thoughts and feelings." ha, what a load of crap. whatever. (please note 'mood' below.)

here's a little haiku i jotted down while returning from, well, leadership camp.  i'm not a complete loser (although please note requirement #7 in the above list), the school sent me there because i'm a class officer.

     Under the Waterfall

     Tiny, mobile icycles

     strike upon the worn old stone

     that is your back.

i was originally going to substitute "that is my back" instead of "that is your back" for the last line, but i decided it was more inspiring and

less depressing this way.  i'll pretend you care.

parents driving me insane (is it a bad thing that i cannot wait until school starts just to get away from them?), must allow myself to be sucked into the portal that comforts with unreality: TELEVISION.

ok  first i'd like to say thank you for reading this, i know you must have your reasons even though i don't understand them.  second, my pondering of the day has wound around this thought, which i would like to share with you all.  am i a cliche?  seriously.  if you don't know what i look like, i am a short, asian girl.  i used to wear glasses, and continued to fit the typical "asian girl" profile.
"Asian Girl Profile Requirements"
1.	Glasses.  (check) 
2.	Plays the flute.  (check) 
3.	Plays the piano.  (check) 
4.	Plays the violin.  (no check, but i wanted to play it, except the teacher said it would be difficult for me to learn on account of me being left-handed [lefties RULE!]) 
5.	Wanted to play the violin.  (check *sigh*) 
6.	Gets straight A's.  (check) 
7.	Is hopelessly boring.  (check) 
8.	And finally, loves and obeys her parents.  (ahem, n/a)

well, six out of eight is still pretty serious.  i mean, i feel like i'm being molded to fit perfectly into something, but isn't it supposed to be i'm the one doing the molding?  hmm...curious.  

another typical asian girl characteristic is being polite and kind to her elders.  when i talk to people with seniority over me, (excluding my immediate family), i plaster on this toothpaste-ad smile and slap on an "i'm happy!" mask.  i'm serious, i swear my voice even gets maybe four degrees higher.  i experienced that today.  aunts and uncles galore came over, and needed to put on my asian girl show.  oh well.

oh, by the way, happy new year.  woo hoo.
